// Raw Tenet Symbolic Engine Test (Boolean Satisfiability)
// Direct access to the constraint solver, bypassing the Flux DSL.

// Formulating a raw logic proposition (CNF - Conjunctive Normal Form)
// We declare variables and demand Tenet finds a state that satisfies them.
var P : bool;
var Q : bool;
var R : bool;

// Constraints
assert (P OR Q);
assert (NOT P OR R);
assert (NOT Q OR R);

// Execution:
// Tenet uses symbolic execution to search for a valid truth assignment.
// If R is False, the constraints become impossible to satisfy.
// Tenet will solve this and output: VALID (P=True, Q=False, R=True) or similar valid states.
check_satisfiability();
